  "prompt": "How do I import my Gmail contacts into Skype?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, you can no longer directly import contacts from Gmail into Skype. Microsoft removed this feature some time ago.\n\nHere are the workarounds and alternatives you can use to get your Gmail contacts into Skype:\n\n**1. Export from Gmail, Import into Outlook.com, Sync Outlook.com with Skype:**\n\nThis is the most common and generally recommended method. It leverages the fact that Skype heavily integrates with Microsoft accounts and services.\n\n*   **Step 1: Export Your Gmail Contacts as a CSV File:**\n    *   Go to [https://contacts.google.com/](https://contacts.google.com/) in your web browser and sign in to your Google account.\n    *   Click the three vertical dots (More actions) near the top of the page (or find an \"Export\" option in the sidebar).\n    *   Choose **\"Google CSV (for importing into a Google account)\"**. (This is generally the best format for compatibility, even though we aren't importing *into* a Google account).\n    *   Click **\"Export.\"**  The file `contacts.csv` will be downloaded to your computer.\n\n*   **Step 2: Import the CSV File into Outlook.com (Microsoft Account):**\n    *   Go to [https://outlook.live.com/](https://outlook.live.com/) and sign in to your Microsoft account (the same one you use for Skype).  If you don't have a Microsoft account, create one.\n    *   Click the **\"People\"** icon in the left sidebar (it looks like two silhouettes).\n    *   Click **\"Manage\"** then select **\"Import Contacts.\"**  (Sometimes the \"Import Contacts\" is in the top ribbon menu)\n    *   Choose **\"CSV\"**.\n    *   Click **\"Browse\"** and locate the `contacts.csv` file you downloaded in Step 1.\n    *   Click **\"Import.\"**\n\n*   **Step 3:  Ensure Skype is Syncing with your Microsoft Account (Outlook.com):**\n    *   Open Skype.\n    *   Click on your profile picture or name.\n    *   Go to **Settings** (usually found under \"...\")\n    *   Go to **Contacts**.\n    *   Make sure the \"Sync your contacts\" or \"Sync contacts from Outlook\" option is enabled.  The exact wording may vary depending on your Skype version.  Sometimes, you need to unlink, then relink your Microsoft account.\n\n    *   **Important:**  It may take some time for Skype to sync your contacts. Give it a few minutes to an hour, depending on the number of contacts.  Restarting Skype can sometimes speed up the process.\n\n**2. Manually Add Contacts (Tedious, but always works):**\n\n*   In Skype, click the **\"New Contact\"** button.\n*   Enter the person's Skype Name, email address, or phone number.\n*   Send a contact request.\n\n**3. Using Third-Party Contact Management Tools (Use with Caution):**\n\n*   There *may* be third-party tools that claim to facilitate contact migration between services. **Use these with extreme caution!**  Many are outdated, unreliable, or could pose a security risk to your accounts.  I cannot recommend specific ones because of these risks.  Thoroughly research any tool before granting it access to your accounts.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Skype Name vs. Phone Number/Email:** Skype prefers connecting via Skype Names (unique usernames). If your Gmail contacts only have phone numbers or email addresses, the connection might not be as seamless. If the person on the other end isn't already on Skype with their email or phone number connected to their profile, they won't show up in Skype even after you add the contact.\n*   **Privacy:** Be mindful of sharing your contacts between services. Understand the privacy policies of Google, Microsoft, and Skype.\n*   **Microsoft Account:** Using a Microsoft account is almost essential for getting the most out of Skype these days.  Make sure you understand how your contacts are being synced and used within the Microsoft ecosystem.\n*   **Skype Versions:** The Skype interface and settings can change over time. If the instructions above don't perfectly match your Skype version, look for similar options or consult Skype's official help documentation.\n\nIn summary, while direct Gmail to Skype import is gone, exporting from Gmail to Outlook.com and then syncing Outlook.com with Skype is the most reliable way to achieve the desired result. Remember to be patient with the syncing process.\n",
